Package ru.spbau.mit.commands

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Command  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Assignment
    The Assignment class implements an internal Shell's command for updating environment with new variable-value pair provided by user by entering "variable=value" command.
    Cat
    The Cat class implements the command that prints file or standard input to output.
    Echo
    The Echo class implements the command that prints its arguments with a space delimeter to its standard output.
    Exit
    The Exit class implements the command that exits the Shell.
    ExternalProcess
    The ExternalProcess class is an internal shell Command for trying to launch an External Process.
    Pwd
    The Pwd class implements the command that prints current working directory path to its standard output.
    Wc
    The Wc class implements the command that outputs for its input: 1.
